ENTRY            F0589   20260225   20260508   20260508       F108
SUBENT        F0589001   20260225   20260508   20260508       F108
BIB                 12         32
TITLE      Cross sections for non-Rutherford backscattering of
           4He from some light elements.
AUTHOR     (C.Huansheng,S.Hao,Y.Fujia,T.Jiayong)
REFERENCE  (J,CNP,15,333,1993)
INSTITUTE  (3CPRFUD)
FACILITY   (VDGT,3CPRFUD)
SAMPLE     The Si target is a natural abundant SiO thin film
            (10 ug/cm2) deposited on a self-supporting carbon film
            (10 ug/cm2) and overcoated with 6 nm Ag.
MONITOR   1(13-AL-27(P,G)14-SI-28,,DA)
          2(8-O-16(A,EL)8-O-16,,DA)
          3(6-C-12(A,EL)6-C-12,,DA)
          4(13-AL-27(P,N)14-SI-27,,DA)
            The energy of beam used for analysis was calibrated
           by resonances of 27Al(p,gamma)28Si reaction at 992 keV,
           16O(alpha,alpha)16O reaction at 3.034 MeV,
           12C(alpha,alpha)12C reaction at 4.625 MeV, and
           27Al(p,n)27Si reaction at 5.803 MeV.
MONIT-REF  (C0091002,J.A.Leavitt+,J,NIM/B,44,260,1990)
           (C0748002,J.A.Leavitt+,J,NIM/B,40-41,776,1989)
DETECTOR   (SIBAR) Two surface barrier detectors were used. One
           was a partially depleted type with small sensitive area
            (25 mm2) and an energy resolution of 15 keV for 2 MeV
           4He ions. The other was an annular configuration with
           a sensitive area of 140 mm2 and an energy resolution of
           25 keV for 2 MeV 4He ions.
ADD-RES    Cross sections for backscattering of high energy 4He
           ions from O, F and Cl were measured.
ERR-ANALYS (DATA-ERR) Typical uncertainties. No information about
           source of uncertainty.
HISTORY    (20031022C)
           (20260225U) SD: Corrections in all Subents.
ENDBIB              32
COMMON               9          6
DATA-ERR   EN-NRM    1EN-NRM    2EN-NRM    3EN-NRM    4ANG
EN-ERR-DIG ERR-DIG    ANG-ERR
PER-CENT   MEV        MEV        MEV        MEV        ADEG
MEV        NO-DIM     ADEG
 2.5        0.992      3.034      4.625      5.803     170.
 0.003      0.004      1.5
ENDCOMMON            6
ENDSUBENT           42
SUBENT        F0589002   20260225   20260508   20260508       F108
BIB                  3          3
REACTION   (14-SI-28(A,EL)14-SI-28,,DA,,RTH)
STATUS     (CURVE,,C.Huansheng+,J,CNP,15,333,1993) Fig.1
HISTORY    (20260225U) SD: STATUS updated.
ENDBIB               3
